  "prompt": "What is airbnb all about?",
  "response": "Airbnb is an online marketplace and hospitality service that allows individuals to list, discover, and book unique accommodations around the world. Here are key points about Airbnb:\n\n1. Accommodation Types\n- Entire homes\n- Private rooms\n- Shared rooms\n- Unique spaces like treehouses, boats, etc.\n\n2. How It Works\n- Hosts list their spaces on the platform\n- Travelers can search and book accommodations\n- Hosts set their own prices and house rules\n- Guests pay through the Airbnb platform\n\n3. Key Features\n- Verified user profiles\n- Reviews and ratings system\n- Secure payment processing\n- Customer support\n- Cancellation policies\n\n4. Benefits\n- Often cheaper than traditional hotels\n- More diverse accommodation options\n- Local, personalized experience\n- Flexibility in location and price range\n\n5. Global Presence\n- Available in over 220 countries\n- Millions of listings worldwide\n- Supports various languages and currencies\n\n6. Additional Services\n- Experiences (local tours and activities)\n- Business travel options\n- Long-term stays\n\nAirbnb essentially connects travelers with local hosts who offer alternative lodging experiences, disrupting traditional hospitality and tourism models.",
